es. Do you think that Holt could be interested in signing an agreement with me along these lines (concerning the three books: Solus Rex, the new novel and the short stories) allowing a sufficient yearly advance to take care of me and my family of two, while I attend to the business of writing?

Very sincerely yours,





TO: FREDERICK STARR1

CC, 1 p.





8 Craigie Circle

Cambridge 38, Mass.

22nd October 1946

Dear Mr. Starr,

